pageContext.claim: “I disagree with the head of the Fed. I'm not -- I'm not happy with what that is because he's kept interest rates. President Obama didn't have near the numbers. And yet, if you look at what happened, he was paying zero. We're paying interest.”
pageContext.analysis: Obama took office during a recession, when the Fed was keeping interest rates near zero to spur badly needed economic growth. Trump took office during a period of sustained growth.
